  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We develop a gluing procedure designed to obtain canonical metrics on connected sums of Einstein four-manifolds. The main application is an existence result, using two well-known Einstein manifolds as building blocks: the Fubini–Study metric on <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">CP</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> and the product metric on <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> . Using these metrics in various gluing configurations, toric-invariant critical metrics are found on connected sums for a specific Riemannian functional, which depends on the global geometry of the factors. Furthermore, using certain quotients of <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> as one of the gluing factors, critical metrics on several non-simply-connected manifolds are also obtained.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
